Wellesley County was named in honour of Governor General of Inon Richard Colley Wellesley , Marquis Wellesley (1760-1842).

Wellesley County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located along the border with Victoria , with the Snowy River part of the northern boundary. It includes Bombala .
